So lively, in fact, that at the end of the evening they were refused several taxi rides home before finally catching a cab. Alan and husband Paul Drayton announced in January this year they were splitting up after three years of marriage. They had been together for 13 years. A statement said: “They have jointly and amicably made the difficult decision.” Radio 2 star Rylan Clark has reportedly been helping Alan through the separation, having recently split with his own husband. Interior Design Masters host Alan also has a new BBC project to look forward to – a property show with Amanda Holden.